The head office of the Kaduna State Independent Electoral Commission (KADSIECOM) has been gutted by fire on Saturday morning less than a month to the conduct of local government elections in the state. Our correspondent gathered that the fire started around 10am but as at 11:24am when our correspondent visited the scene, Â the top floor of the building was seen in flames, with fire fighters battling to put out the inferno as trucks of the state fire fighting unit were seen driving in.